Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["The Stabilizer Formalism, by Computation", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"a83fa342-6a4e-4814-b076-31488527c51f"],

Cell["\<\
This document teaches the stabilizer formalism the way one would teach it at \
a chalkboard with a kernel open: every claim is immediately computed. We \
start from the observation that a single qubit can be specified not by its \
two amplitudes but by the one operator that fixes it, build that idea into \
the Aaronson-Gottesman tableau, and ride it all the way to thousand-qubit \
Clifford circuits, error-correcting codes, graph states, magic states, and \
Clifford channels. We close with a measured, honest comparison against the \
specialized C++ and Julia stabilizer simulators.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c0431861-3191-4a1e-a21e-afb8be865749"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The arc is: a state is what stabilizes it (single qubit), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c61abdc7-95d8-46f1-876a-37a274424c45"],
 " generators replace ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bcc29501-5006-48aa-aa1b-dd9bd8e5d889"],
 " amplitudes (the tableau), entanglement and measurement become linear \
algebra over ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\|01d53d", "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b7637405-af8d-4ab2-8316-1f37214ce364"],
 ", and then scale, codes, and the frontier. The audience is graduate \
students who know quantum mechanics and the Pauli group but have not yet seen \
why a stabilizer state of a thousand qubits is something you can hold in your \
hand. Everything below is built explicitly so you can change it, break it, \
and extend it. The Wolfram QuantumFramework symbols we exercise live in the \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Wolfram"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "17c915cb-b3bc-4ad6-83fe-20b25c99abf7"],
 "QuantumFramework",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"`", " ", "paclet"}], ";", " ", 
   RowBox[{"the", " ", "central", " ", "one", " ", 
    RowBox[{"is", " ", "["}]}]}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "c0ee22a2-41ed-47e7-bb85-592de3f307ea"],
 "PauliStabilizer`]."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bce13bba-2133-4d89-a4d5-6cdf7bfbe6de"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ed06d5f3-ce75-491e-ba99-449999c03aab"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We load the framework from the working tree so the fast paths and recent \
fixes are present. On a current release, the plain ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Needs"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "803d3b54-1b71-4852-a581-aed74dbde05a"],
 " line alone suffices."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"560db299-223d-4117-b65e-00c5d78b5b5d"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"PacletInstall", "[", 
  RowBox[{"\"\<https://www.wolfr.am/DevWQCF\>\"", ",", 
   RowBox[{"ForceVersionInstall", "->", "True"}]}], "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"<<", "Wolfram`QuantumFramework`"}]}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.990789204067354*^9},ExpressionUUID->"b674d13a-f43f-4a39-900d-\
7ccb092af70f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The core functions at a glance", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b2f51b77-d483-41a0-9223-cd30e9a4ab36"],

Cell["\<\
Before the narrative, the whole working surface, grouped by task. Every call \
is exercised in context later; this is the map.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d91c712e-f454-4d09-b56e-63c7f392a1ff"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Construct", "TI"],
 " a register, from signed Pauli strings, a named code, or a random Clifford: \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "n", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "220d40c2-3150-473f-b539-de740bfac81d"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<XX\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"60787031-6f9d-4d13-928f-939265e103d3"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "\"\<SteaneCode\>\"", "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"d474d3f9-7e17-4c9b-95fc-8aed278df325"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Random\>\"", "[", "n", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"8bda8afe-6268-4130-9332-e3d4be3917cc"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"86b57625-b278-4db2-8331-fbb46f37ff4c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Apply a Clifford gate", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"e21c5e1b-4d30-429e-9883-c6e584410cbf"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<S\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"456140ed-ca6e-4fd5-af1e-38ea887b62ba"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"7eb6581d-2de0-4f00-8f51-c32ce6cb3cc0"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CZ\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"22e086da-394b-49f0-8eb5-fa325f1a4813"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
